---
import SectionLabel from './SectionLabel.astro';
---

<section class="py-24 px-4">
  <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
    <SectionLabel number="05" title="How It Works" />
    <p class="text-text-secondary text-lg mb-12 max-w-2xl">
      Rúnar transforms high-level contract code into optimized Bitcoin Script through a multi-stage compilation pipeline.
    </p>

    <!-- Pipeline diagram -->
    <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row items-stretch gap-0 overflow-x-auto pb-4">
      {[
        { label: 'Source Code', sub: 'TS / Go / Rust', color: 'text-accent-500' },
        { label: 'Parser', sub: 'Language-specific', color: 'text-text-secondary' },
        { label: 'AST', sub: 'Typed tree', color: 'text-text-secondary' },
        { label: 'IR', sub: 'Intermediate repr', color: 'text-text-secondary' },
        { label: 'Optimizer', sub: 'Size & fees', color: 'text-text-secondary' },
        { label: 'Bitcoin Script', sub: 'OP_CODES', color: 'text-accent-500' },
      ].map((stage, i, arr) => (
        <div class="flex items-center">
          <div class="flex flex-col items-center text-center px-4 py-6 min-w-[120px]">
            <div class:list={['font-mono text-sm font-semibold', stage.color]}>{stage.label}</div>
            <div class="text-xs text-text-tertiary mt-1">{stage.sub}</div>
          </div>
          {i < arr.length - 1 && (
            <div class="hidden md:block text-text-tertiary px-1">
              <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
                <polyline points="9 18 15 12 9 6" />
              </svg>
            </div>
          )}
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>

    <div class="mt-8 p-6 rounded-xl bg-surface border border-border">
      <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
        Each source language has its own parser, but all converge on a shared intermediate representation (IR). The optimizer works on this IR to minimize script size and execution cost before emitting final Bitcoin Script opcodes. The result is a deterministic, auditable output that can be deployed directly to BSV.
      </p>
      <a href="/docs/compiler/how-it-works" class="inline-block mt-4 text-sm text-accent-500 hover:underline">
        Learn more about the compiler &rarr;
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
